    <text id="B0008T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Crawford and Brock announce that their committee will be ready to begin building
                    a church as soon as they have lumber, but that they need Jackson to submit the
                    order.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr Jackson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-03-02">March 2<hi rend="super">d</hi> 68</date>
                        <name type="place">Waynesboro</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>We the committe for building the Church in this place are ready to commence work.</p>

                <p>Mr. Watts says he is "ready to deliver the lumber and wants an order from you."
                    Will you please give us one for the bill of lumber.</p>

                <p>We don't know any thing about what Harry Keys has done or what arrangements he
                    has made with you. Please let us know how it stands now, so we will know what to
                    do. All we lack is the lumber. Will be much obliged to you for an order for it. </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>John Crawford <lb/>Archy Brock<lb/><abbr expan="Committee"
                    >Commt</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
